And just when I was ready to give up, @vijayshreejewels stepped in like magic ✨

Not revealing what I picked just yet… but I promise it completes the Parna look like nothing else 💛

First things first – nails done, mood set! 💅✨
Nothing kicks off Parna prep like sitting back and watching your nails go from basic to beautiful. The tiniest details feel so important when it’s for your big day. I went with something elegant and clean – just the way I like it.
Tell me I’m not the only one who feels like they’ve got their life together the moment their nails are done? 😅💖

Also, huge shoutout to @happyfingers.10 💖 Just wanted to say a big thank you for the amazing nails!
Both my sister and I absolutely loved them 💅 Your work and your service were just perfect!
Thank you so much for being so patient with me and for bringing my design to life exactly how I imagined it.
Also, really appreciate you coming home at the last minute and helping out – that meant a lot.
You guys are so talented and kind — can’t wait for our next session already! ♥️💘

latestPosts.caption:
This wasn’t a vacation… it was a pause. A little mini escape that felt like a lifetime of memories. 🧿💖

From Mumbai to Surat, back and forth, up and down—emotionally and literally. 🌆🚗✨

@sayami_kothari got rookafied, I got rookafied, and @krishiikothari got engaged—so yeah, lots of bling and happy tears. 💍🥹
One hell of a month for KOTHARI SISTER’s💘🧿

Met the kindest souls, danced like nobody was watching (garba back in motion 🩰), stuffed myself with food and desserts like there’s no tomorrow 🍰🍕🍩, and just lived in the moment.

Met old friends, made new memories, spoke my heart out, got to know people better. Fell in love a little deeper, laughed a little louder, healed a little more. 💬🫶

Had endless family lunches and dinners, my brand @tasty_cakebake turned 5 years too, celebrated Nani’s ghar Derasar’s 26th birthday like it was our little world. 👵🏽🥰

Caught the best sunset in Mumbai. And somewhere between all the chaos and calm—I entered my happy girl era. 🌅👑

Yes, I even cried. But sometimes you need to feel it all to realize you’re living your best life.
This month? It was everything. Literally everything. 🧿💫

latestPosts.caption:
5 years ago, I had nothing but a hand mixer, a tiny kitchen, and a BIG dream — to turn my love for baking into something real. 💭💗

I never imagined that from one cake order, it would turn into hundreds… then thousands. That people would trust me with their birthdays, proposals, baby showers, even break-up cakes (yes, that happened 😂).

Behind every cake was a late night, a nervous moment, a happy tear, or a little dance when a customer said “This is PERFECT!” 🥹💃🏻

Today, I’m not just celebrating a brand milestone — I’m celebrating you. Every single one of you who placed an order, shared a post, referred a friend, or simply believed in this journey. 🤍

From the bottom of my mixing bowl — thank you. Here’s to more cakes, more chaos, and much more sweetness ahead! 🧁✨

#5YearsOftastycakebake🎂
